cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image-text matching tasks, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed neural network architectures involve learning similarity between the two modalities, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses neighborhood sampling and similarity scores, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
